title: The Gate of the Feral Gods
author: Matt Dinniman

title: The Eye of the Bedlam Bride
author: Matt Dinniman

title: The Wedding People
author: Alison Espach
notes: Never thought I'd cry about a wedding book, but the book was hilarious and about a woman kind of becoming herself again. English Professor, extremely funny and emotional in a way I didn't expect.

title: Careless People
author: Naomi Klein
notes: A must read book about Facebook, privacy, and our democracy. The audiobook is read by the author herself (who is a Kiwi, so has a nice accent!)

title: The Faculty Lounge
author: Roger Rosenblatt
notes: Good fun book about educators in a wacky overall situation, told from many points of view. A light read and enjoyable.

title: Chain Gang All Stars
author: Nana Kwame Adjei-Brenyah
notes: The ending felt lack-luster, but the concept was good and it brings in new emotional feelings about the justice system and the concepts of good and evil, as well as restorative justice.

title: Annie Bot
author: Sierra Greer
notes: Expected more, but was pretty good considering the premise was very extensive.

title: The People We Keep
author: Allison Larkin
notes: Book about a musician who travels around after escaping her abusive family, learns to kind of be herself. It was okay, but didn't live up to what I wanted.

title: The Lost Bookshop
author: Evie Woods
notes: This book was good, but two months later I can't remember anything about it.
